      "description": "This 1995 Mazda RX-7 is an impeccably preserved example of Japanese engineering. The 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine maintains factory-spec compression, delivering a linear power band across the RPM range. The five-speed manual gearbox offers crisp, short-throw engagement, paired with a perfectly balanced 50/50 weight distribution and a Torsen limited-slip differential. The chassis remains exceptionally rigid, supported by its original double-wishbone suspension and four-piston aluminum calipers. Every vacuum line and solenoid has been inspected, ensuring the complex sequential boost transition is seamless. This is a true collector-grade specimen with zero thermal degradation or aesthetic fatigue.",
